{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I want to argue to you that in fact, politics and religion,"},{"time":5000,"text":"which are the two primary factors --"},{"time":7000,"text":"not the sole, but overwhelmingly, the primary factors --"},{"time":10000,"text":"which are driving towards a war which looks extremely likely --"},{"time":13000,"text":"bordering on the inevitable at this point,"},{"time":15000,"text":"whether one is in favor of that or not --"},{"time":17000,"text":"that politics and religion are, in fact, themselves"},{"time":20000,"text":"better conceptualized as kinds of technology,"},{"time":24000,"text":"and subject to kinds of questions that we regularly consider"},{"time":29000,"text":"in the space of conceptual design."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32000,"text":"Here's what I mean. Politics and --"},{"time":35000,"text":"let's focus on the political system in particular question here,"},{"time":38000,"text":"which is the system of democracy."},{"time":40000,"text":"Democracy, as a type of politics, is a technology"},{"time":44000,"text":"for the control and deployment of power."},{"time":46000,"text":"You can deploy power in a wide range of ways."},{"time":49000,"text":"The famous ones -- despotism is a good one;"},{"time":51000,"text":"anarchy is a way to not deploy the power in any organized way,"},{"time":54000,"text":"to do it in a radically diffused fashion;"},{"time":56000,"text":"and democracy is a set of technologies,"},{"time":58000,"text":"which have the effect of, in principle,"},{"time":61000,"text":"diffusing the power source to a large number of people"},{"time":64000,"text":"and then re-concentrating it in a smaller group of people who govern,"},{"time":67000,"text":"and who themselves are, in principle, authorized to govern"},{"time":71000,"text":"by virtue of what the broader public has done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"Now, consider religion -- in this case Islam,"},{"time":77000,"text":"which is the religion that, in some direct sense,"},{"time":80000,"text":"can be said to be precipitating what we're about to enter."},{"time":84000,"text":"Let me say parenthetically why I think that's the case,"},{"time":86000,"text":"because I think it's a potentially controversial statement."},{"time":89000,"text":"I would put it in the following equation: no 9/11, no war."},{"time":93000,"text":"At the beginning of the Bush administration,"},{"time":97000,"text":"when President Bush, now President Bush, was running for president,"},{"time":100000,"text":"he made it very clear that he was not interested in intervening broadly in the world."},{"time":103000,"text":"In fact, the trend was for disengagement with the rest of the world."},{"time":106000,"text":"That's why we heard about the backing away from the Kyoto protocol, for example."},{"time":110000,"text":"After 9/11, the tables were turned."},{"time":113000,"text":"And the president decided, with his advisors,"},{"time":116000,"text":"to undertake some kind of an active intervention in the world around us."},{"time":120000,"text":"That began with Afghanistan,"},{"time":122000,"text":"and when Afghanistan went extremely smoothly and quickly,"},{"time":125000,"text":"a decision was made through the technology of democracy --"},{"time":129000,"text":"again, notice, not a perfect technology --"},{"time":132000,"text":"but through the technology of democracy"},{"time":134000,"text":"that this administration was going to push in the direction of another war --"},{"time":137000,"text":"this time, a war in Iraq."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"Now, the reason I begin by saying \"no 9/11, no war\""},{"time":144000,"text":"is that we have to acknowledge that Islam,"},{"time":148000,"text":"as interpreted by a very, very small, extremely radical group of people,"},{"time":154000,"text":"was a precipitating cause of the 9/11 attacks --"},{"time":158000,"text":"the precipitating cause of the 9/11 attacks --"},{"time":160000,"text":"and as a consequence, at one degree of remove,"},{"time":163000,"text":"the precipitating cause of the coming war that we're about to be engaged in."},{"time":167000,"text":"And I would add that bin Laden and his followers"},{"time":170000,"text":"are consciously devoted to the goal of creating a conflict between democracy,"},{"time":175000,"text":"or at least capitalist democracy, on the one hand,"},{"time":178000,"text":"and the world of Islam as they see and define it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182000,"text":"Now, how is Islam a technology in this conceptual apparatus?"},{"time":185000,"text":"Well, it's a technology for, first, salvation in its most basic sense."},{"time":189000,"text":"It's meant to be a mechanism for construing the universe"},{"time":192000,"text":"in a way that will bring about the salvation of the individual believer,"},{"time":196000,"text":"but it's also meant by the Islamists --"},{"time":198000,"text":"and I use that term to mean people who believe that Islam --"},{"time":202000,"text":"they follow the slogan, Islam is the answer to a wide range of questions,"},{"time":205000,"text":"whether they're social, or political, or personal, or spiritual."},{"time":208000,"text":"Within the sphere of people who have that view,"},{"time":210000,"text":"and it's a large number of people in the Muslim world"},{"time":212000,"text":"who disagree with bin Laden in his application,"},{"time":214000,"text":"but agree that Islam is the answer."},{"time":216000,"text":"Islam represents a way of engaging the world"},{"time":219000,"text":"through which one can achieve certain desirable goals."},{"time":222000,"text":"And the goals from the perspective of Muslims are, in principle,"},{"time":226000,"text":"peace, justice and equality,"},{"time":229000,"text":"but on terms that correspond to traditional Muslim teachings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233000,"text":"Now, I don't want to leave a misimpression"},{"time":236000,"text":"by identifying either of these propositions --"},{"time":239000,"text":"rather, either of these phenomena, democracy or Islam -- as technologies."},{"time":243000,"text":"I don't want to suggest that they are a single thing that you can point to."},{"time":246000,"text":"And I think a good way to prove this"},{"time":248000,"text":"is simply to demonstrate to you what my thought process was"},{"time":251000,"text":"when deciding what to put on the wall behind me when I spoke."},{"time":254000,"text":"And I ran immediately into a conceptual problem:"},{"time":256000,"text":"you can't show a picture of democracy."},{"time":258000,"text":"You can show a slogan, or a symbol, or a sign that stands for democracy."},{"time":263000,"text":"You can show the Capitol --"},{"time":264000,"text":"I had the same problem when I was designing the cover"},{"time":266000,"text":"of my forthcoming book, in fact --"},{"time":268000,"text":"what do you put on the cover to show democracy?"},{"time":270000,"text":"And the same problem with respect to Islam."},{"time":272000,"text":"You can show a mosque, or you can show worshippers,"},{"time":274000,"text":"but there's not a straightforward way of depicting Islam."},{"time":276000,"text":"That's because these are the kinds of concepts"},{"time":278000,"text":"that are not susceptible to easy representation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"Now, it follows from that, that they're deeply contestable."},{"time":284000,"text":"It follows from that that all of the people in the world"},{"time":287000,"text":"who say that they are Muslims can, in principle,"},{"time":289000,"text":"subscribe to a wide range of different interpretations"},{"time":292000,"text":"of what Islam really is, and the same is true of democracy."},{"time":297000,"text":"In other words, unlike the word hope,"},{"time":300000,"text":"which one could look up in a dictionary and derive origins for,"},{"time":304000,"text":"and, perhaps, reach some kind of a consensual use analysis,"},{"time":307000,"text":"these are essentially contested concepts."},{"time":309000,"text":"They're ideas about which people disagree in the deepest possible sense."},{"time":315000,"text":"And as a consequence of this disagreement,"},{"time":318000,"text":"it's very, very difficult for anyone to say,"},{"time":320000,"text":"\"I have the right version of Islam.\""},{"time":322000,"text":"You know, post-9/11, we were treated to the amazing phenomenon"},{"time":325000,"text":"of George W. Bush saying, \"Islam means peace.\""},{"time":328000,"text":"Well, so says George W. Bush."},{"time":331000,"text":"Other people would say it means something else."},{"time":333000,"text":"Some people would say that Islam means submission."},{"time":335000,"text":"Other people would say it means an acknowledgement"},{"time":337000,"text":"or recognition of God's sovereignty."},{"time":339000,"text":"There are a wide range of different things that Islam can mean."},{"time":342000,"text":"And ostensibly, the same is true of democracy."},{"time":344000,"text":"Some people say that democracy consists basically in elections."},{"time":347000,"text":"Other people say no, that's not enough,"},{"time":349000,"text":"there have to be basic liberal rights: free speech, free press, equality of citizens."},{"time":353000,"text":"These are contested points, and it's impossible to answer them by saying,"},{"time":356000,"text":"\"Ah ha, I looked in the right place, and I found out what these concepts mean.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":360000,"text":"Now, if Islam and democracy are at present"},{"time":364000,"text":"in a moment of great confrontation,"},{"time":366000,"text":"what does that mean?"},{"time":368000,"text":"Well, you could fit it into a range of different interpretative frameworks."},{"time":372000,"text":"You could begin with the one that we began with a couple of days ago,"},{"time":375000,"text":"which was fear."},{"time":377000,"text":"Fear is not an implausible reaction with a war just around the corner"},{"time":382000,"text":"and with a very, very high likelihood that many, many people are going to die"},{"time":385000,"text":"as a consequence of this confrontation --"},{"time":387000,"text":"a confrontation which many, many people"},{"time":389000,"text":"in the Muslim world do not want,"},{"time":391000,"text":"many, many people in the American democracy do not want,"},{"time":394000,"text":"many people elsewhere in the world do not want,"},{"time":396000,"text":"but which nonetheless is favored by a large enough number of people --"},{"time":399000,"text":"at least in the relevant space, which is the United States --"},{"time":403000,"text":"to actually go forward. So fear is not a crazy response at all."},{"time":406000,"text":"And I think that that's, in fact, probably the first appropriate response."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"What I want to suggest to you, though, in the next couple of minutes"},{"time":413000,"text":"is that there's also a hopeful response to this."},{"time":417000,"text":"And the hopeful response derives from recognizing"},{"time":420000,"text":"that Islam and democracy are technologies."},{"time":422000,"text":"And by virtue of being technologies, they're manipulable."},{"time":425000,"text":"And they're manipulable in ways"},{"time":427000,"text":"that can produce some extremely positive outcomes."},{"time":429000,"text":"What do I have in mind?"},{"time":431000,"text":"Well, all over the Muslim world there are people"},{"time":434000,"text":"who take Islam deeply seriously, people who care about Islam,"},{"time":438000,"text":"for whom it's a source either of faith, or of civilization, or of deep values,"},{"time":442000,"text":"or just a source of powerful personal identity,"},{"time":444000,"text":"who think and are saying loudly that Islam and democracy"},{"time":448000,"text":"are in fact not in conflict, but are in fact deeply compatible."},{"time":452000,"text":"And these Muslims -- and it's the vast majority of Muslims --"},{"time":455000,"text":"disagree profoundly with bin Laden's approach, profoundly."},{"time":460000,"text":"And they furthermore think overwhelmingly --"},{"time":463000,"text":"again one can't speak of every person, but overwhelmingly,"},{"time":465000,"text":"and one can find this by reading any of the sources"},{"time":467000,"text":"that they have produced, and they're all over the Internet"},{"time":470000,"text":"and in all sorts of languages -- one can see that they're saying"},{"time":473000,"text":"that their concern in their own countries is primarily to free up themselves"},{"time":479000,"text":"to have choice in the spheres of personal life,"},{"time":483000,"text":"in the sphere of economics, in the sphere of politics,"},{"time":486000,"text":"and, yes, in the sphere of religion,"},{"time":488000,"text":"which is itself closely regulated in most of the Muslim world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491000,"text":"And many of these Muslims further say"},{"time":493000,"text":"that their disagreement with the United States"},{"time":496000,"text":"is that it, in the past and still in the present,"},{"time":499000,"text":"has sided with autocratic rulers in the Muslim world"},{"time":503000,"text":"in order to promote America's short-term interests."},{"time":509000,"text":"Now, during the Cold War, that may have been"},{"time":511000,"text":"a defensible position for the United States to take."},{"time":513000,"text":"That's an academic question."},{"time":515000,"text":"It may be that there was a great war to be fought between West and East,"},{"time":518000,"text":"and it was necessary on the axis of democracy against communism."},{"time":522000,"text":"And it was necessary in some way for these to contradict each other,"},{"time":525000,"text":"and as a consequence you have to make friends wherever you can get them."},{"time":528000,"text":"But now that the Cold War is over,"},{"time":530000,"text":"there's nearly universal consensus in the Muslim world --"},{"time":534000,"text":"and pretty close to the same here in the United States,"},{"time":536000,"text":"if you talk to people and ask them --"},{"time":538000,"text":"that in principle, there's no reason that democracy and Islam cannot co-exist."},{"time":542000,"text":"And we see this among activist, practical Muslims,"},{"time":545000,"text":"like the Muslims who are presently the elected,"},{"time":547000,"text":"parliamentary, democratic government of Turkey,"},{"time":549000,"text":"who are behaving pragmatically, not ideologically,"},{"time":552000,"text":"who are promoting their own religious values,"},{"time":554000,"text":"who are elected by their own people"},{"time":556000,"text":"because they were perceived as honest and sincere"},{"time":558000,"text":"because of their religious values,"},{"time":560000,"text":"but who do not think that Islam and a democratic system of governance"},{"time":564000,"text":"are fundamentally incompatible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566000,"text":"Now, you may say, but surely, what we've seen on television about Saudi Islam"},{"time":571000,"text":"convinces us that it can't possibly be compatible"},{"time":573000,"text":"with what we consider the core of democracy --"},{"time":575000,"text":"namely, free political choice, basic liberty and basic equality."},{"time":579000,"text":"But I'm here to tell you that technologies"},{"time":583000,"text":"are more malleable than that."},{"time":585000,"text":"I'm here to tell you that many, many Muslims believe --"},{"time":588000,"text":"the vast majority, in fact -- in fact I think I would go so far as to say"},{"time":590000,"text":"that many Muslims in Saudi Arabia believe that the core values of Islam,"},{"time":594000,"text":"namely acknowledgement of God's sovereignty"},{"time":596000,"text":"and basic human equality before God,"},{"time":599000,"text":"are themselves compatible with liberty, equality and free political choice."},{"time":603000,"text":"And there are Muslims, many Muslims out there, who are saying precisely this."},{"time":608000,"text":"And they're making this argument wherever they're permitted to make it."},{"time":611000,"text":"But their governments, needless to say, are relatively threatened by this."},{"time":613000,"text":"And for the most part try to stop them from making this argument."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616000,"text":"So, for example, a group of young activists in Egypt"},{"time":620000,"text":"try to form a party known as the Center Party,"},{"time":622000,"text":"which advocated the compatibility of Islam and democracy."},{"time":624000,"text":"They weren't even allowed to form a party."},{"time":626000,"text":"They were actually blocked from even forming a party"},{"time":628000,"text":"under the political system there. Why?"},{"time":630000,"text":"Because they would have done extraordinarily well."},{"time":632000,"text":"In the most recent elections in the Muslim world --"},{"time":634000,"text":"which are those in Pakistan, those in Morocco"},{"time":637000,"text":"and those in Turkey -- in each case,"},{"time":639000,"text":"people who present themselves to the electorate as Islamic democrats"},{"time":642000,"text":"were far and away the most successful vote-getters"},{"time":645000,"text":"every place they were allowed to run freely."},{"time":649000,"text":"So in Morocco, for example, they finished third in the political race"},{"time":653000,"text":"but they were only allowed to contest half the seats."},{"time":655000,"text":"So had they contested a larger number of the seats,"},{"time":657000,"text":"they would have done even better."},{"time":659000,"text":"Now what I want to suggest to you is that the reason for hope in this case"},{"time":662000,"text":"is that we are on the edge of a real transformation in the Muslim world."},{"time":667000,"text":"And that's a transformation in which many sincerely believing Muslims --"},{"time":671000,"text":"who care very, very deeply about their traditions,"},{"time":674000,"text":"who do not want to compromise those values --"},{"time":677000,"text":"believe, through the malleability of the technology of democracy"},{"time":681000,"text":"and the malleability and synthetic capability of the technology of Islam,"},{"time":686000,"text":"that these two ideas can work together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689000,"text":"Now what would that look like?"},{"time":691000,"text":"What does it mean to say that there's an Islamic democracy?"},{"time":694000,"text":"Well, one thing is, it's not going to look identical"},{"time":696000,"text":"to democracy as we know it in the United States."},{"time":699000,"text":"That may be a good thing, in light of some of the criticisms we've heard today --"},{"time":702000,"text":"for example, in the regulatory context -- of what democracy produces."},{"time":706000,"text":"It will also not look exactly the way either the people in this room,"},{"time":710000,"text":"or Muslims out in the rest of the world --"},{"time":712000,"text":"I don't mean to imply there aren't Muslims here, there probably are --"},{"time":715000,"text":"conceptualize Islam."},{"time":717000,"text":"It will be transformative of Islam as well."},{"time":720000,"text":"And as a result of this convergence,"},{"time":723000,"text":"this synthetic attempt to make sense of these two ideas together,"},{"time":727000,"text":"there's a real possibility that, instead of a clash"},{"time":730000,"text":"of Islamic civilization -- if there is such a thing --"},{"time":733000,"text":"and democratic civilization -- if there is such a thing --"},{"time":735000,"text":"we'll in fact have close compatibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"Now, I began with the war because it's the elephant in the room,"},{"time":742000,"text":"and you can't pretend that there isn't about to be a war"},{"time":744000,"text":"if you're talking about these issues."},{"time":746000,"text":"The war has tremendous risks for the model that I'm describing"},{"time":749000,"text":"because it's very possible that as a consequence of a war,"},{"time":752000,"text":"many Muslims will conclude that the United States"},{"time":755000,"text":"is not the kind of place that they want to emulate"},{"time":757000,"text":"with respect to its forms of political government."},{"time":760000,"text":"On the other hand, there's a further possibility that many Americans,"},{"time":763000,"text":"swept up in the fever of a war, will say, and feel, and think"},{"time":768000,"text":"that Islam is the enemy somehow --"},{"time":770000,"text":"that Islam ought to be construed as the enemy."},{"time":773000,"text":"And even though, for political tactical reasons,"},{"time":775000,"text":"the president has been very, very good about saying that Islam is not the enemy,"},{"time":779000,"text":"nonetheless, there's a natural impulse when one enters war"},{"time":782000,"text":"to think of the other side as an enemy."},{"time":784000,"text":"And one furthermore has the impulse to generalize, as much as possible,"},{"time":787000,"text":"in defining who that enemy is."},{"time":789000,"text":"So the risks are very great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791000,"text":"On the other hand, the capacities for positive results in the aftermath of a war"},{"time":798000,"text":"are also not to be underestimated,"},{"time":800000,"text":"even by, and I would say especially by, people"},{"time":803000,"text":"who are deeply skeptical about whether we should go to war in the first place."},{"time":806000,"text":"Those who oppose the war ought to realize that if a war happens,"},{"time":811000,"text":"it cannot be the right strategy,"},{"time":813000,"text":"either pragmatically, or spiritually, or morally, to say after the war,"},{"time":819000,"text":"\"Well, let's let it all run itself out, and play out however it wants to play out,"},{"time":822000,"text":"because we opposed the war in the first place.\""},{"time":824000,"text":"That's not the way human circumstances operate."},{"time":826000,"text":"You face the circumstances you have in front of you"},{"time":828000,"text":"and you go forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830000,"text":"Well, what I'm here to say then is,"},{"time":832000,"text":"for people who are skeptical about the war,"},{"time":834000,"text":"it's especially important to recognize that in the aftermath of the war"},{"time":837000,"text":"there is a possibility for the government of the United States"},{"time":841000,"text":"and the Muslim peoples with whom it interacts"},{"time":844000,"text":"to create real forms of government that are truly democratic"},{"time":847000,"text":"and also truly Islamic."},{"time":849000,"text":"And it is crucial -- it is crucial in a practical, activist way --"},{"time":853000,"text":"for people who care about these issues to make sure"},{"time":857000,"text":"that within the technology of democracy, in this system,"},{"time":860000,"text":"they exercise their preferences, their choices and their voices"},{"time":863000,"text":"to encourage that outcome."},{"time":865000,"text":"That's a hopeful message,"},{"time":867000,"text":"but it's a message that's hopeful only if you understand it"},{"time":869000,"text":"as incurring serious obligation for all of us."},{"time":872000,"text":"And I think that we are capable of taking on that obligation,"},{"time":875000,"text":"but only if we put what we can into it."},{"time":878000,"text":"And if we do, then I don't think that the hope will be unwarranted altogether."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882000,"text":"Thanks."}]}]}